{{Infobox TV channel | name = Argent | logofile = Argent logo.svg | logocaption = '''Argent logo''' | launch = February 21, 2005 | closed date = April 30, 2016 | picture format = [[480i]] ([[Standard-definition television|SDTV]]) | network = | owner = [[Groupe TVA]] | slogan = | country = [[Canada]] | broadcast area = National | headquarters = [[Montreal]], [[Quebec]] | former names = | replaced names = | sister names = | timeshift names = }} '''Argent''' (''Money'') was a [[Television in Canada|Canadian]] [[French language]] [[Category A services|Category A]] [[specialty channel]]. The channel was devoted to business news and [[finance|financial]] information. The channel was owned and operated by [[Groupe TVA]], a division of [[Quebecor Media]]. It was the francophone counterpart of [[Business News Network]].
==History== On November 24, 2000, a consortium of companies including Groupe TVA (50.1%), Publications Transcontinental Inc. (30%) and BCE Media Inc. (19.9%) was granted a broadcasting licence by the [[Canadian Radio-television and Telecommunications Commission]] (CRTC) for a television channel called ''LCN Affaires'', described as "a national French-language Category 1 specialty television service devoted to business and personal finance."<ref>[http://www.crtc.gc.ca/eng/archive/2000/DB2000-468.htm Decision CRTC 2000-468] CRTC 2000-12-14</ref>
Before the channel was launched, Groupe TVA bought the remaining shares from the other partners, bringing its ownership to 100%. Shortly thereafter, the channel was launched on February 21, 2005 as "Argent".<ref>[http://tva.canoe.ca/groupetva/communiques/326.html LA PREMIÈRE CHAÎNE FINANCIÈRE FRANCOPHONE EN AMÉRIQUE DU NORD] Groupe TVA press release 2005-02-16 {{fr icon}}</ref>
On April 19, 2016, Quebecor announced that Argent would cease broadcasting after April 30, 2016. The company cited the channel's poor profitability as justification for the decision.<ref name="gandm-argentshutdown">{{cite web|title=Quebecor Media's TVA Group closing business channel Argent|url=https://www.theglobeandmail.com/report-on-business/quebecor-medias-tva-group-closing-business-channel-argent/article29673259/|website=The Globe and Mail|accessdate=19 April 2016}}</ref>
