'''Gildardo Gutierrez Mendez''' -(b. [[Guadalajara]], March 15, 1982) is a Mexican business activist and entrepreneur. He promotes Mexican causes in Mexico and the United States. He serves on the Boards of Educational Foundations and Institutions. He actively promoted international education agreements and foreign direct investment in Mexico.

== Career ==
He founded multiple companies and advises their Boards of Director. He founded the Asociacion de EmpresariosMexicanos (AEM) in [[Washington DC]]. He promoted the change of the Mexico narrative in the United States,focusing on "building bridges" between the two countries through collaboration with public and private sectors.

Gutierrez is the author of ''FuturoEducativoDistritos'' (2013) (Educational Future: School Districts) in which he makes the case for education system decentralization in Mexico, parent involvement in school activities and school district implementation. The book has been presented in several academic institutions and think tanks in Mexico and the United States, including the [[Brookings Institution]]. Gildardo authored papers including the Education Series for the Mexico Institute at the Woodrow Wilson Center for International Scholars.

