'''Harald Arnkværn''' (born 5 February 1939) is a Norwegian barrister and businessperson.

He was born in [[Oslo]]. He [[Examen artium|finished]] his secondary education in 1957 and took the [[cand.jur.]] degree in 1964. He was a deputy judge in [[Ringerike District Court]] from 1964 to 1965, then a junior solicitor from 1965 to 1972 with a study leave at the [[University of Illinois Law School]] from 1967 to 1968. He took the lawyer's license in 1966 and was a barrister (a lawyer with access to [[Supreme Court of Norway|Supreme Court]] cases) from 1972.<ref name=dagb01>{{cite news|title=Ukeslutt|date=4 November 2001|work=Dagbladet|page=25|language=Norwegian}}</ref>

He was employed in [[Christiania Spigerverk]] from 1965 to 1974 and [[Den norske Creditbank]] from 1974 to 1988. In 1988 he was acting chief executive officer of DnC. He then continued his career as a barrister<ref name=snl>{{cite encyclopedia|year=|title=Harald Arnkværn|encyclopedia=[[Store norske leksikon]]|editor=|publisher=Kunnskapsforlaget|location=Oslo|url=http://www.snl.no/Harald_Arnkværn|language=Norwegian|accessdate=19 July 2011}}</ref> in the law firm [[Haavind Vislie]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Valgte Arnkværn|last=Bjerkholt|first=Bård|author2=Riisnæs, Ida Grieg|date=15 May 2001|work=Dagens Næringsliv|page=6|language=Norwegian}}</ref>

He succeeded [[Knut Rasmussen (barrister)|Knut Rasmussen]] as chair of the supervisory council in [[UNI Storebrand]] in 1992.<ref>{{cite news|title=Han skal gjenreise tilliten til UNI|date=11 August 1992|author=Sandvik, Per Ivar|work=[[Aftenposten]]|page=23}}</ref> He has also been chair of [[Christiania Bank og Kreditkasse]] from 1996 to 2001, [[Kværner]], [[Vinmonopolet]], [[Schøyen Gruppen]], the [[Norwegian Guarantee Institute for Export Credits]], [[Fjellinjen]], [[A. Falkenberg Eftf.]] and Afas. He became corporate council leader in the [[Orkla Group]] in 2001.<ref name=dagb01/><ref name=snl/>

